The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 2: Maruti Suzuki India has raised the prices of all its models, expect Alto, by up to Rs 7,500, citing a sharp increase in input costs. The new prices are applicable with immediate effect. Because of a sharp increase in the input costs, Maruti Suzuki India has decided to pass on a part of this cost impact to customers, the company said.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 2: The government has set the issue price of Engineers India Ltds (EIL) follow-on public offer at Rs 290 per share. This will be the upper end of the price band. A discount of 5 per cent will be given to retail bidders and to employees, official sources said.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 2: Steel Authority of India (SAIL) will appoint up to six merchant bankers to advise it on the timing of the first tranche of its share-sale programme, through which it expects to raise Rs 8,000 crore.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 2: The government has decided to increase the benchmark price for exporting onions by $20 to $220 a tonne in August to discourage overseas shipments as prices in the domestic market have gone up.                             
	 Calcutta, Aug. 2: Allahabad Bank has raised fixed deposit rates by up to a maximum of 125 basis points. The new rates for deposits below Rs 1 crore will be effective from August 2, while for those above Rs 1 crore are effective from July 29.
                                                                                                                          
